g.title: EleanorRank2Convo5 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank2Convo5 begins.

g.title: j285924268
g.text: Hey, Eleanor...

g.title: j3263754652
g.text: Hey. What’s on your mind?

g.title: j4274380427
g.text: You were a ‘journalist’, right? What’s one of those exactly?

g.title: j590844886
g.text: Nothing much. [End.]

g.title: j2659727807
g.text: Someone who turns other people’s trauma into cash.

g.title: j4251476585
g.text: I.

g.title: j4118119996
g.text: Got it. We call those ‘Corpus’.

g.title: j2127172605
g.text: Check boolean EleanorOrigin

g.title: j3194149274
g.text: You -

g.title: j1165717814
g.text: Oh Gods. Sorry. I was being facetious.

g.title: j2127172605->j1165717814
g.text: true

g.title: j1937844789
g.text: Let me try again.

g.title: j2127172605->j1937844789
g.text: false

g.title: j1571052044
g.text: You started this...

g.title: j1920850208
g.text: A journalist is someone who hunts down interesting things that are happening in the world and tells other people about them, either by writing or making a broadcast of some sort. Usually both.

g.title: j1005113373
g.text: Perplexing creature...

g.title: j2870248272
g.text: A storyteller, I suppose. But not the sort who makes things up.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j534351914
g.text: So what makes a story ‘interesting’?

g.title: j3726325745
g.text: So you only tell the truth? How do you pick which truths to tell?

g.title: j3314372649
g.text: Most of the time, people are interested in reading about the bad things that happen in the world. If it bleeds it leads, as the saying goes.

g.title: j3811007674
g.text: I can’t imagine the situation’s any different in your time.

g.title: j1631831937
g.text: I tried to make a difference with my work. Yes, I was getting paid for it, but I wanted to do good in the world, too.

g.title: j2916376111
g.text: Check boolean EleanorHatesHeroes

g.title: j1371159940
g.text: I was younger then, of course. Nothing cures you of the drive to 'do good in the world' than spending some time in it.

g.title: j2916376111->j1371159940
g.text: true

g.title: j143436171
g.text: This is where it got me. Literally. I only came here to Höllvania in the first place because of the story.

g.title: j2916376111->j143436171
g.text: false

g.title: j1902572057
g.text: Sorry. Sidetracked. Need to rant. Are you up for listening to me sound off about a pet hate of mine?

g.title: j61114983
g.text: I thought you were here because Arthur was.

g.title: j1654257474
g.text: Sure, why not.

g.title: j1074658428
g.text: Honestly, no. [End.]

g.title: j3527244580
g.text: Oh, he was here first. But he made the mistake of telling me what was happening here, and I couldn’t sit on it. So I place a call to my old friend Danny MacIlvoy and pay over the odds for a forged visa and passport. Because I need them in a hurry.

g.title: j4071817721
g.text: Ok. Don't say I didn't warn you. I have a theory I call the Hero Virus.

g.title: j281104486
g.text: You have to understand: they were locking Höllvania down, but they couldn’t do it all at once. This may be a walled city-state that’s been here since the time of the Radiant Khan, but the walls they put up to fend her off are old now and the powers in charge couldn’t get barricades and checkpoints up in time.

g.title: j2709626225
g.text: Just imagine for a moment that you can have a virus that's transmitted through stories. Like all viruses it wants to take over the host and spread itself further.

g.title: j2813963887
g.text: People were falling over themselves to get out. So nobody paid much attention to one stupid Britannic girl who was trying to get in.

g.title: j210437493
g.text: The Hero Virus makes you see the world as if it were a story. It persuades you that Good is all about INDIVIDUAL PEOPLE doing AWESOME THINGS

g.title: j1849295671
g.text: You want to know the worst part?

g.title: j4021721849
g.text: So naturally you want to be one of those people

g.title: j345195555
g.text: Tell me the worst part.

g.title: j1957894509
g.text: Is it going to be gross?

g.title: j2206736827
g.text: No matter how tough it may be

g.title: j3396571822
g.text: Okay. Here is the worst part.

g.title: j2662585709
g.text: Oh, and we suddenly become squeamish?

g.title: j959212846
g.text: Because a Hero has to make hard decisions. A Hero has to endure pain stoically.

g.title: j3932910906
g.text: I was investigating an outbreak of what was being called Testudo Syndrome. Testudo because it means turtle, and people who had it were developing tough patches on their skin as an early marker. The same sort of thing that eventually turns into armour plating in us lucky few.

g.title: j973417910
g.text: Pardon me for upsetting your delicate sensibilities. Never mind, then.

g.title: j3323969127
g.text: It's all such cynical bullshit. The Hero Virus exists to sell toys, market movies and to make little boys and girls grow up to be willing cannon fodder

g.title: j2059921747
g.text: Testudo Syndrome was a treatment-resistant disease that seemed to be exclusive to Höllvania, had some enigmatic and sinister connection to computers, and appeared all at once. And people who asked too many questions about it had a tendency to end up as a clog in a Höllvanian sewer pipe.

g.title: j2561526501
g.text: They don't make films about the Chosen One whose heroic destiny is to wipe old people's bums in a nursing home

g.title: j221423648
g.text: Within hours of getting into Höllvania I was picking my way through the sewers and talking Arthur down from the biggest emotional fit he has ever been on.

g.title: j3033819903
g.text: I'm almost done, stay with me

g.title: j2178797402
g.text: That boy. You would think I’d followed him here just to piss him off.

g.title: j2609487635
g.text: The Hero Virus tricks you into thinking that you can do the most good if there's a spotlight on you. It sets an impossible, twisted example

g.title: j4081077655
g.text: Sounds like you didn't take the situation seriously.

g.title: j2022542638
g.text: Admit it. You did.

g.title: j1608026303
g.text: No, but it *was* a bonus, wasn't it?

g.title: j3816782033
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j2013115221
g.text: I bloody did take it seriously.

g.title: j3189817948
g.text: Of course I did. But I also had a noble purpose in mind.

g.title: j3344934062
g.text: Precisely. But I also had a noble purpose in mind.

g.title: j676101515
g.text: Arthur thinks he's losing me to the Techrot. But the truth is, I lost him to the Hero Virus a long time ago.

g.title: j3782242147
g.text: People were trying to kill me. Forgive me for having a sense of humour about it.

g.title: j2670726640
g.text: ‘Noble.’ Sol’s balls. I really deserved everything that happened to me, didn’t I?

g.title: j3440758730
g.text: Boolean EleanorHeroVirus is now true.

g.title: j3698886531
g.text: Maybe you've just been on your own for too long, but in an outfit like this, taking the piss out of one another helps keep us sane.

g.title: j4180043559
g.text: You were telling me about the worst part.

g.title: j3241016851
g.text: Sounds like you were just doing your job. What happened next?

g.title: j2694040789
g.text: I admit, sometimes it gets too close to the bone, especially when Lettie is in one of her depressive slumps and needs someone to hate on

g.title: j2539641666
g.text: Right, right.

g.title: j3002900362
g.text: So I’m in the sewers, and something with a cluster of CRT monitors instead of a head goes lurching past. I’ve barely finished shitting myself when I find the nest.

g.title: j3454821129
g.text: But please, for all our sakes, lighten up a bit.

g.title: j863243033
g.text: Growths. Part organic, part technology, part some poor bastard’s delerium tremens. Light in the kind of colours people only see when they’ve inhaled too many solvent fumes. It’s hideous and I can’t take my eyes off it.

g.title: j2879025764
g.text: Even Arthur pops open a beer and puts his feet up, once in a while.

g.title: j1107583173
g.text: Jackpot, I think.

g.title: j2083377388
g.text: Oh no...

g.title: j1244115426
g.text: Tell me you didn't stay there.

g.title: j1085634482
g.text: I take a dozen grainy pictures on my Kinematic 2300A slip-phone and I send the pictures to Arthur.

g.title: j3258824394
g.text: Of course I did.

g.title: j2806288574
g.text: And I say ‘Think I’ve found where this Techrot is coming from.’

g.title: j1599366326
g.text: I filed the story the next day. ‘The Techrot Beneath Höllvanian Streets.’

g.title: j2617822830
g.text: You named it.

g.title: j3576020735
g.text: So that's where that came from.

g.title: j4241987332
g.text: Ta-da! I named it.

g.title: j4214326247
g.text: There it is. The worst part.

g.title: j3295228217
g.text: Nobody calls it ‘Testudo Syndrome’ now. Nobody calls it the Technocyte. Everyone just calls it Techrot.

g.title: j2539140206
g.text: I named the thing that’s eaten this city and is eating me from the bones outward.

g.title: j1265973904
g.text: Boolean EleanorHollTold is now true.

g.title: j386575185
g.text: Play stupid games, win stupid prizes, I guess?

g.title: j2542696536
g.text: What’s so bad about that? The name fits.

g.title: j1951744838
g.text: Sorry. For some reason I thought you'd understand. Or at least sympathize.

g.title: j1390722598
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j3145042129
g.text: You're right, though. It IS all a stupid game, isn't it

g.title: j4025580120
g.text: Nobody talks about the work I did on Minister Jeremy Coniston and the bogus famine relief, or the Lazlo Fertilizer scandal, or any of that. It barely made a ripple.

g.title: j1930810608
g.text: We're all just a bunch of decaying clowns trapped on a carousel that never stops

g.title: j531430915
g.text: And now I come up with a term that everyone uses and nobody even knows I came up with it.

g.title: j3262121946
g.text: Roll up roll up see the amazing gorgon lady, one of a kind, don't let your child come too close madam, she's not been fed today

g.title: j3683247656
g.text: ‘Techrot’

g.title: j515748213
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j1337628468
g.text: They can put that word on my bloody tombstone.

g.title: j4082424688
g.text: Talk whenever. Need a drink.

g.title: j4243608736
g.text: If I get one.
